caption: They always have my food ready when I get there and are professional. Best chinese food I've had and lots of nonmeat, tasty vegetable options!
Best Chinese restaurant Bloomington has to offer! Grew up walking down there to pick up dinner in the summertime! Always looking forward to the next time I order from there!💪🏼
Best Chinese food in the US! Simply perfect authentic Chinese food. Love the family as well, such good people. My family has loved them for 20 years!
By far the best Chinese food in B town
Good inexpensive Asian food
Best Cheap Chinese Ever!
Tasty

Dragon Express may be the best Chinese food in Bloomington! Tonight, I had the Chicken with Cashews with Roast Pork Fried Rice. My wife had Szechuan Chicken and Eggplant. Both were great. While the food is wonderful, the ambience isn't great. And it's cash or checks only; no credit or debit cards. Enjoy!

I'm giving them four stars because they fill a nitch in btown for chinese food you will find in any small town USA, the food may not be authentic Chinese, but sometimes you just want that old fashioned chinese food from the 90's, loaded with msg, sugar and that brown sauce that is a standard in about every dish.

I'm addicted to this place. The lunch n dinner combos are the way to go. Add pork the fried rice for $1. Eggplant with garlic sauce is of my favorite go tos. Pictured is chicken with Chinese vegetables dinner combo special (with pork fried rice upgrade.)
Excellent. Only problem is when the younger family members are there to take your order they are very rude. No thank you. No smile. Just take your food and get out attitude. Tends to ruin it.
Reliably good Chinese food. Glad that they are open again, if only for carry out.
Great food at a good price. Definitely one of, if not my most, favorite spots in town for Chinese food that suits my anglicized palate.

Another place they're eager to please. Great food, not a long wait and they aren't messing around in the kitchen!! These guys are there faithfully day in and day out. Always smiling, always friendly.. A bit hard to understand at times, but who isn't right? Worth the drive to get great Chinese. I recommend the happy family, excellent food for the price!! As long as I'm near Bloomington, I'll eat here on a regular. Really, check em out!!
This place has the best Sweet and Sour Chicken I have ever had and I spent 3 months eating with solely chop sticks if that says anything about my experience with oriental foods. Great Place to Munch
Tasty dishes, generous portions and reasonable prices! Cash and checks only, no credit cards.
It's one of my favourite Chinese restaurants. I like their house tofu.
I'm disappointed they stopped putting pork in their fried rice with the dinner combination specials
Quick, good pad thai vegetable with friendly service. Bring cash or check. No plastic accepted. Ask for chopsticks if you want them.
Good location with good American Chinese food.
Great service great prices. Fantastic food
Food is always good, and cheap.
They give you so much hot and fresh food for a cheap price!

In my opinion, this is the worst Chinese food I’ve ever had in my life, it is so bad that even the “fake Chinese food” restaurant like Panda Express is better than them. As a restaurant which is so close to the residence hall, they really don’t value this good location...
It's the Dragon. Consistent western Chinese food.

This is a solid place. Great selection and the food quality is consistently good. Only once in the many times I've visited have I waited a long time for my meal. The prices are competitive too. I favor the shrimp with hot pepper sauce! The hunan shrimp is a good choice as well!
I am going to rate this 5 star, even though I took the trouble of withdrawing money from ATM to visit this place. So you can trust me that this place is worth the trouble of paying in cash.
flame. I wish I had figures this place out a few years ago when I moved here.  Always taste good and freshly made, and always served quickly...
I have been going to Dragon Express since 2012 and have NEVER gotten a bad meal. Their food is always hot and delicious.
Dragon is awesome.

I've come here many times while I've lived in Bloomington. It's a pretty average Chinese place, but I enjoy the food even if it is a bit greasy sometimes like an average Chinese place. I mostly go because of the convenient campus location, but I'd recommend it for a decent quick bite. Just don't forget it's cash or check only!
Good food for reasonable prices
Decent entrees, good price
Fast, friendly staff and good food
Really good Chinese and great value. My only complaint is that they don't take credit cards so I can go more often :)
Great place for some good chinese food that is easy on your wallet.
It's a good place to get reasonably priced food. Very nice people, clean, and decent food. What more can you ask for?
Great food shrimp sweet and sour
Your typical run-of-the-mill hometown Chinese restaurant. Not spectacular but still tasty with large portions for the price. The eggrolls were great.
Slow but good
Reasonable price and good take out.
I’ve been coming here since 2004. Consistently great food, fast service! I especially love their mu shu, but everything’s good.
Affordable quality food.
Always a stop going through town!

Dragon express is like many other chinese places in bloomington-- quick and casual. The place is a bit old and slightly unclean, but that doesn't make the food bad. I highly reccomend the pad thai (not exactly chinese, but good). I wish they accepted card, but it's cash only.
Decent American Chinese food. Not traditional or healthy, but tastes allright.

How do you know if a Chinese restaurant is good? That's easy. A busy restaurant with poor service. This place hits the mark. The service may be bad at times, but the food is always excellent and will keep you coming back for more.
👍🏿Hebrew brown guy from Florida I bought some food last night it tasted amazing the restaurant was clean I’m gonna have to rate 5 stars.

Go-to Chinese place!

Very good food for a very good price. I like that the kitchen staff will adapt a recipe if I ask for it due to allergies and personal taste. Thanks for the quick service every time we've ordered over the past 25 years!
a Bloomington classic
This place is fast, tasty, and inexpensive. One of my favorites.
This is a good place to eat if you want to call in sick at work tomorrow.

Very nice staff member. Always willing to engage with the customers.
Best Chinese-American fast food in Bloomington without question. Unbelievably large menu. My go to carryout food
Great food, nice service 10/10
Fast service and good food

A pillar of the Bloomington restaurant community. Quite possibly the best Chinese food west of Xinjiang.
Cheap decent food. Broccoli and tofu is my favorite dish.
Best Chinese takeout in town. With students gone, there was no wait.
This is really great quality of food. The aroma just draws everyone in. I definitely recommend this place.

Pretty good. Super cheap for the amount of food you get and the food quality is pretty good. Great for take out - very close to campus and easy to get to from surrounding neighborhoods. For cheap Chinese (and i mean cheap) this is it.

Great prices. Get small for dinning in. Bigger serving, then take out.
Close to campus. Food wasn't what I expected but decent anyways. Tried it twice.

Only complaint is the cash only thing. Very good other than that
Quick service, decent prices, quality and quanity food for price.

Very tasty lo mein, I used to live near here and went there all the time. Everyone is very nice and the prices are reasonable. It is cash only but definitely still worth it.

Good solid Chinese restaurant close to campus. Nothing fancy but good food at a good price.
The Dragon Express is a Bloomington treasure. It's delicious, cheap, and fresh! I love the general Tso's chicken,  crab Rangoon, dumplings, and hot and sour soup. Keep up the good work Dragon! :)

Typical brown sauce bland ethnic joint. They do offer some real China dishes on a separate menu. I stick with the vegatavle lo mein, the dumplings and the double cooked spicy pork (because it is actually somewhat spicy and has lots of cabbage in it).

So far, the best Chinese food I have found in Bloomington. Favorites include hot and sour soup, crab rangoon, steamed dumplings, and curry beef. Got the pork fried rice and it tasted like it got burnt/too hot. Hopefully, an isolated incident.
They have the best general tso chicken.
Do you want cheap Chinese food that meets all the requirements of cheap Chinese food? If so, you can't go wrong at the dragon. My tip for tofu dishes, ask for extra crispy tofu.
For someone below, teriyaki is a cooking method of Japanese curisne… not Chinese…
Good food, not very clean looking.
Good fried rice and BBQ pork. Staff has no emotion.
Decent cheap Chinese food. And they deliver!
Hella Good Food!
Flavorless and disgusting. Felt violated.
They don't have Teriyaki chicken... And they call themselves Chinese...

(NOTE: CASH ONLY) Five years ago, I would have easily given this place a 4 or even a 4.5, but now, the quality is so low.  They rush their orders so much that they BARELY cook their chicken anymore -- it is borderline RAW most of the time.  The old owner retired, and the new people just don't seem like they have the same passion as the old man did.  It's alright in a pinch, but definitely no longer one of the better Chinese food places in town.
Best General Tzo's chicken in Bloomington.

Worst Chinese I've ever had in my life. Got the chicken chow mein and the noodles were stale and it had zero flavor. Also got the chicken lo mein and it was horrid. Zero flavor. Never going back. I had a little bit and packed the rest up and threw it in the trash.

Everything is extremely hot, but once it cools it is some of the best Chinese takeout in town.  This and noodle town are the only places I know of that serve chow fun in Bloominton, a sweet flat noodles dish.  Never had a disappointing meal and the price is great.
Best Chinese in Bloomington. General Chicken dinner special for under $7 is hard to beat with such good food.
We can't think of a better place to fill our tummies. :)
